ct information you provide to us, to make you aware of new features and Services related to the Autobrain System. </p> <p> <strong> <u>Children’s Privacy. </u></strong> The Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act imposes certain requirements on websites directed at children under 13 that collect information on those children, and on websites that knowingly 3collect information on children under 13. Our site is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13. </p> <p> <strong><u>Protection of Personal Information.</u></strong> We make reasonable efforts to maintain the security, integrity and privacy of any personal information you choose to give us. All personal information is stored on our Internet database and/or servers. Access to personal information is limited to those individuals who are authorized to use such information for business and administrative purposes. Although we will strive to take appropriate measures to safeguard against unauthorized disclosures of information, we cannot assure you that personally identifiable information that we collect will never be disclosed in a manner inconsistent with this Privacy Policy. Inadvertent disclosures may occur. </p> <p> <strong><u>Security of Personal Information on Other Websites.</u></strong> Our websites contains links to sites operated by third parties that are not under our control or supervision. Neither we nor our employees, agents or representatives are responsible for the privacy practices of these sites. These sites may have their own privacy policies and customer service policies, or no policies at all. We encourage you to read the privacy policies of the other sites to see how your personal information will be handled on the third party sites before providing them with your personal information. </p> <p> <strong><u>Changes to the Personal Information We Have Collected.</u></strong>If you would like us to remove your personal information from our database, please send us an email request to <a href=\"mailto:privacy@autobrain.com\"><u>privacy@autobrain.com</u></a> Registered users of our site and service can access, review and edit their registration information, including login information, contact information, billing information and other suitable information, on our site. If you would like to delete your registration information, you can email us at <a href=\"mailto:privacy@autobrain.com\"><u>privacy@autobrain.com</u></a> Please be aware, however, that even after your request for deletion is processed, we may, for a time, retain residual information about you in backup and/or archival copies of our database. </p> <p> <strong><u>Applicable Law</u></strong> The laws of the State of New York will govern this Privacy Policy without giving effect to any principles of conflict of law. </p> <p> <strong><u>Effective Date and Modifications.</u></strong>This policy is effective as of October, 2015. Please note that we may modify this Privacy Policy at any time, at our sole discretion, by posting the modified policy on our website. The modifications will be effective upon posting, unless some other date is specified. You should review this Privacy Policy periodically so that you are aware of any modifications. Your use of any of our website constitutes your full acceptance of the Privacy Policy in its then-current form. </p> <p> <strong><u>Termination.</u></strong> Upon terminating your Account, we will retain your information, including personal, vehicle and payment information, for as long as reasonably needed, and to comply with all applicable laws, regulations and policies. </p> <p> <strong><u>Questions or Comments.</u></strong> If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy, you may contact us at <a href=\"mailto:privacy@autobrain.com\"><u>privacy@autobrain.com</u></a> <br/> <br/> <strong><u>Terms of Use.</u></strong> This Privacy Policy forms a portion of the Terms of Use. Any disputes relating to this Privacy Policy are subject to the provisions of the Terms of Use. If you do not consent to this Privacy Policy and the Terms of Use, please do not access the Autobrain System. <br/> </p> </div> </div>"
    
    let dataTextView: UITextView = {
        let label = UITextView()
        label.isEditable = false
        return label
    }()
    
    let doneButton: UIButton = {
        let button = UIButton()
        button.backgroundColor = PRIMARY_COLOR_PURPLE
        button.setTitleColor(.white, for: .normal)
        button.setTitle("Done", for: .normal)
        button.titleLabel?.font = UIFont.systemFont(ofSize: 18, weight: UIFont.Weight.regular)
        button.addTarget(nil, action: #selector(handleDonePressed), for: .touchUpInside)
        return button
    }()
    
    override func viewDidLoad() {
        super.viewDidLoad()
        
        view.backgroundColor = .white
        view.accessibilityIdentifier = "termsView"
        
        var htmlData = NSString(string: termsString).data(using: String.Encoding.unicode.rawValue)
        switch(documentType) {
        case .terms:
            break
        case .privacy:
            htmlData = NSString(string: privacyString).data(using: String.Encoding.unicode.rawValue)
            break
        }
        
        let attributedString = try! NSAttributedString(data: htmlData!, options: convertToNSAttributedStringDocumentReadingOptionKeyDictionary([convertFromNSAttributedStringDocumentAttributeKey(NSAttributedString.DocumentAttributeKey.documentType): convertFromNSAttributedStringDocumentType(NSAttributedString.DocumentType.html)]), documentAttributes: nil)
        dataTextView.attributedText = attributedString
        
        view.addSubview(dataTextView)
        view.addSubview(doneButton)
        
        _ = dataTextView.anchor(view.topAnchor, left: view.leftAnchor, bottom: view.bottomAnchor, right: view.rightAnchor, topConstant: 20, leftConstant: 16, bottomConstant: 44, rightConstant: 16, widthConstant: 0, heightConstant: 0)
        _ = doneButton.anchor(dataTextView.bottomAnchor, left: view.leftAnchor, bottom: view.bottomAnchor, right: view.rightAnchor, topConstant: 0, leftConstant: 0, bottomConstant: 0, rightConstant: 0, widthConstant: 0, heightConstant: 0)
        
    }
    
    @objc func handleDonePressed() {
        dismiss(animated: true, completion: nil)
    }
}

